Introduction

ABLUE is a six-member boy group under J-Star Entertainment. They will make their debut on October 22, 2022, with the single album "Carnival".

On May 13, 2024, J-Star announced that Win.L has left the group due to health reasons and ABLUE will continue as six members.

As of March 2025, ABLUE has entered an indefinite hiatus due to multiple members preparing for or currently fulfilling their mandatory military service. With some enlistment schedules still unconfirmed, the group has concluded their current season of activities and will take time to resolve all military-related matters. The decision was made in consideration of both the members' duties and the company’s long-term planning. Fans are encouraged to continue supporting the members as they fulfill their national responsibilities.
